<node TEXT="ELF: when calling a fucntion in shared lib1. call a predefined function (puts@plt)2. in puts@plt, jump to GOT+offset3. initially, GOT+offset is the second following line of above jump. By this means, GOT says the function location has not been resolved yet. 4. puts@plt then calls the _dl_runtime_resolve which finds the location of the function and saves the location in GOT+offset, so next time this function is called, we&apos;ll get the address in above step 2." ID="Freemind_Link_1997792888" CREATED="1227012089666" MODIFIED="1227012651106"/>
</node>
